      "raw_text": "H. E. Craig brought suit in the\nsuperior court against the Spokane\ne Inland Empire railway to col\nlect $4,000 damages for personal\ninjuries while employed as brake\nman in December, 1906 Craig,\nwho knew nothing of electricity,\nwas set to repair a trolley. He\nwas shocked so terribly, he says,\nhe will be cripple the rest of his\nlife."
